				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: haste and slow stacking?<a name="66918"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Oct 14 04 4:03 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>The haste has been covered...
<br />

<br />
When I am pulling for a raid (or group) , for instance, and they are hard hitting mobs, I equip my drum to get a max debuff, so my second song, a slow, is more likely to land.
<br />

<br />
I don't often swap instruments during melee, but pulling or down time (when we've taken a beating), I will. If we have a another slower who is having trouble landing a slow, I'll swap the drum back in for a debuff.
<br />

<br />
Since, as was said before, instruments don't affect haste or slow %'s, just debuff amounts and stat boosts....you have to consider how your group is buffed. In an upper level group with shammy buffs, they may be maxed with your songs NOT instrument modded (maybe even before your songs) so no need to swap in.
<br />

<br />
At lower levels where you might be affecting 3 or more melees who aren't max stated, you might very well be more beneficial to the group swapping instruments and slugging the mob. It takes dedication, but thats what you'd do for maximum effectiveness. 
<br />

<br />
Being a bit of a swapper myself, I still only two two instruments, which is just a one click swap for me, but I have know bards who will swap three.
<br />
</span></td>
