				<td colspan="2"><span>They reason why you slow on the pull -- it may not matter much at level 50, but on raids now, we are fighting mobs that hit for over 3K and can rampage.  You NEED the rampage to be on a rampage tank and you need the agro to be on the main tank.  If an enchanter, shaman, or beastlord slows that mob before it makes contact with the main tank, they WILL get agro.  If they land slow within the first 5 seconds or so, before rampage and agro are set, they WILL get agro.  If they get agro, bad things happen.  Debuffers die, the mobs moves out of position, rampage starts hitting people it isn't supposed to, and your raid wipes.  If NO ONE slows for the first 10 seconds of the fight, a quad for 3K will take out pretty much any main tank in the game.  But a bard can land a 55% slow, yield agro instantly to a main tank/RT combination, and you can take a mob like Magmaton and Krziik the mighty and mash him flat with no deaths.  And to make sure this happens, as Spoogy mentioned, you equip your best drum and land OOS/HOS on the pull to set up your slow.</span></td>
