				<td colspan="2"><span><blockquote><b>Quote:</b><br><span class="quote">Any song with a snare component WILL get totally knocked off by a better, higher level snare. That has always been true, as far as I know.</span></blockquote>
<br />
I always thought our song stays active for the normal duration even if a better snare lands.  Gah, I'm second-guessing myself atm.  
<br />

<br />
Regardless, I was referring to the song being knocked off entirely when another class lands a better SLOW.  I'm almost positive this happens with 51 Largo's.  I used to use it alot on inc to stagger mobs that are not lullable.  I could always tell when the dedicated slower lands the spell on the snared mob because I get the worn off message and the mob comes running.  Also, typically the dedicated slower has a chat msg indicating which mob they just slowed.  I just have not tested this recently to confirm it myself.
<br />

